summary.narrativeincludeclinical:
Case number PHEH2011US00469 is an initial spontaneous legal case received from consumer's attorney on 19 Apr 2011 in the form of civil complaint (CV11-3154) and follow up report received on 07 Sep 2012, 05 Oct 2012, 10 Oct 2012, 30 Oct 2012, 28 Nov 2012, 30 Nov 2012 and 05 Dec 2012 from physician via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. This report refers to an adult male patient. The patient was smoker, drinker and allergic to Penicillin, Tetracycline and Ancef. The patient's family history included mother had (uterine cancer and heart disease) father had (thyroid disease, heart disease and osteoarthritis), grandfather had (prostate cancer) and brother died due to AIDS. The patient's surgical history included left inguinal hernia repaired in 1959 and nephrolithiasis in 1971. The patient had medical history of pneumonia and multiple myeloma in (1998). The patient's concomitant medications included Vicodin (hydrocodone bitartrate), Decadron (dexamethasone), Zantac (ranitidine hydrochloride), Pepcid (famotidine), Neurontin (gabapentin), Hytrin (terazosin hydrochloride) were updated. On an unspecified date in 1999 the patient received intravenous Aredia (disodium pamidronate) at a dose of 90 mg monthly (indication not reported). On an unspecified date in 2002 the patient received intravenous Zometa (zoledronate) at a dose of 4 mg monthly (indication not reported). As a result of administration of the drug, the consumer developed osteonecrosis of the jaw, infection, disfigurement, physical injury, pain, suffering, emotional distress, mental anguish and physical disability. In Jul 2002 patient had problem in right jaw. In 2003, the patient had mandibular pain and grave's disease. Record dated 23 Mar 2003 stated that the patient had bronchitis. Record dated 01 Apr 2003 stated that the patient suffered conjunctivitis. Record dated 23 Apr 2003 stated that the patient had viral upper respiratory tract infection and hyperthyroidism. Record dated 05 May 2003 noted tooth abscess. Patient first presented with bisphosphonate related osteonecrosis of right mandible in 2004. Patient completely discontinued Zometa in 2004. Record dated 04 Feb 2004 noted swelling in right socket, numbness in right jaw and osteomyelitis of mandible at the site of extracted tooth. CT scan of the mandible on 05 Feb 2004 revealed a lytic lesion of the right mandible. In Mar 2004 patient received hyperbaric oxygen treatment. Record dated 03 Mar 2004 noted lesion under right jaw and soft raised mass in the right sub mental region. Record dated 29 Apr 2004 noted wound in chin which had started to drain and dry bone exposed. Record dated 21 May 2004 noted hypothyroidism, radio necrosis of right jaw, swelling in his right jaw, extraction of teeth and poor healing of the wound at the site of the teeth extraction with bone exposed area and round papule on the right mandibular border of chin. On Aug 2004, the patient had fistula, internal and external to jaw. Record dated 10 Sep 2004 stated that patient had inflamed gingiva. Record dated 29 Sep 2004 stated that the patient developed facial swelling. Record dated 02 Oct 2004, stated that gram staining was carried out from mandible abscess and it revealed moderate gram positive cocci. On 05 Oct 2004 patient was hospitalised for mandible infection. The records further stated that the patient underwent thyroid replacement and hyperbaric therapy. Record dated 09 Dec 2004 noted normocytic normochromic anemia and atypical lymphoid aggregate. Record dated 15 Dec 2004 noted aseptic necrosis bone. On 10 Feb 2005 culture result revealed moderate growth of candida albicans. On 28 Jun 2005 noted two cysts of each kidney and granulomatous calcification of spleen. Record dated 01 Feb 2006 noted degenerative changes of the carpometacarpal joint. Record dated 17 Feb 2006, noted heart mild bradycardiac. Record dated 11 Apr 2006 noted teeth sensation. Record dated 20 Sep 2006 noted atrial fibrillation. On 26 Sep 2006 noted chronic osteomyelitis and patient underwent molar root canal. Record dated 27 Jun 2007 noted mixed sclerotic and lytic destructive changes within the mandible. Record dated 03 Jul 2007 noted fatigue with jaw osteomyelitis. Record dated 30 Nov 2007 noted hyperopia, astigmatism and presbyopia. Record dated 26 Feb 2008 noted worse cough up blood. On 02 Mar 2008 noted gastro esophageal reflux disease and hypertrophy. Record dated 11 Mar 2008 noted rib fracture on the left. Record dated 30 May 2008 noted cataract right eye. Record dated 22 Aug 2008 noted malaise. Record dated 23 Sep 2008 noted chronic necrotic ulcer at right mandible surface. Record dated 24 Feb 2009 noted fatty infiltration of liver. Record dated 27 Feb 2009 noted memory changes. Record dated 24 Mar 2009 noted that the patient had osteonecrosis of jaw due to Zometa. The records further stated that the patient had osteopenia. Record dated 03 Apr 2009 noted hyperkeratosis. Record dated 20 Apr 2009 noted rhinorrhea. Record dated 21 Apr 2009 noted cat bite to right hand. Record dated 06 Jul 2010 noted that patient had fallen on right hip and had lot of pain. Record dated 03 Nov 2010 stated that patient had toothache. Record dated 19 Nov 2010 patient underwent mandibulectomy. Record dated 16 Dec 2010 noted cellulitis of oral soft tissues. On same record dated again noted right mandibular infection. Record dated 20 Jan 2011 stated that patient had jaw inflamed. Record dated 22 Feb 2011 stated that patient had glaucoma open angle, hypertrophy prostatic benign (BPH), bite of hand infected and thyroiditis. Record further stated that patient underwent thoracic vertebra resection. Patient was hospitalised for sepsis of mandible in Mar 2011. Record dated 02 Mar 2011 noted actinomyces and fungal infection in mandible. Record dated 03 Mar 2011 stated that patient underwent tracheostomy. Record dated 07 Mar 2011 stated that patient segment of mandible with focal erosion and granulation tissue in mandible. Record dated 11 Mar 2011 noted shortness of breath. Record dated 14 Mar 2011 noted leukocytosis. Record dated 15 Mar 2011 noted atelectasis. Dental record dated 15 Mar 2011 stated that patient had postoperative swelling and suture abscess. Record dated 23 Mar 2011 noted dysphagia. Record dated 13 Apr 2011 noted dysarthria and patient underwent speech therapy. In May 2011, the patient had carotid artery occlusion. On 23 May 2011, the patient had carotid artery stenosis and underwent gastrostomy tube placement. Record dated 21 Jul 2011 noted painful onychomycosis. Record dated 08 Sep 2011 noted small retention of cysts in the floor of the left maxillary sinus. Record date 12 Jan 2012 noted teeth missing (32, 31, 30, 29, 28, 23, and 22). Record dated 24 Feb 2012 stated that the patient underwent mandibular reconstruction with fibular flap. Record dated 27 Sep 2012 noted lower urinary tract symptoms. The physician did not provide causality and seriousness criteria for the events. The final outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow up received on 07 Sep 2012: The patient historical condition, concomitant medications and events (hypothyroidism, radio necrosis of right jaw, swelling in his right jaw, extraction of teeth and poor healing of the wound at the site of the teeth extraction with bone exposed this area, round papule on the right mandibular border of chin, thyroid replacement hyperbaric therapy, normocytic normochromic anemia and atypical lymphoid aggregate) were updated.
Combined follow up received on 05 Oct 2012 and 10 Oct 2012 from physician via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. The patient historical condition, procedure and events (Mandibular pain, grave's disease, numbness in right jaw, osteomyelitis mandible in site of extracted tooth, lesion has come up under right jaw, soft raised mass right sub mental region, wound in chin has started to drain, dry bone exposed, fistula, internal and external to jaw, moderate gram positive cocci, mandible infection, moderate growth candida albicans, two cysts of each kidney and granulomatous calcification in spleen, degenerative changes of the carpometacarpal joint, atrial fibrillation, mixed sclerotic and lytic destructive changes within the mandible, fatigue with jaw osteomyelitis, hyperopia, astigmatism and presbyopia, cough up blood, gastro esophageal reflux disease, hypertrophy, rib fracture on the left, malaise, chronic necrotic ulcer surface at right mandible, fatty infiltration of liver, memory changes, osteopenia, hyperkeratosis, rhinorrhea, fallen in right hip having lot of pain, cellulitis of oral soft tissues, right mandibular infection, actinomyces and fungal infection in mandible, shortness of breath, carotid artery stenosis, carotid artery occlusion, cataract right eye, tooth abscess, lytic lesion of the right mandible, teeth sensation, teeth missing (32, 31, 30, 29, 28, 23, and 22) were updated.
Follow up received on 30 Oct 2012 from physician via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: Procedure (mandibular reconstruction with fibular flap) and event (sepsis of mandible) was updated.
Follow-up received on 28 Nov 2012 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Current condition updated (multiple myeloma). Aredia start date was updated. Zometa start date and stop date were updated. Procedures updated (thoracic vertebra resection, tracheostomy and gastrostomy tube placement). Events updated (problem in right jaw, toothache, jaw inflamed, glaucoma open angle, hypertrophy prostatic benign (BPH), bite of hand infected, thyroiditis, segment of mandible with focal erosion and granulation tissue in mandible, postoperative swelling, suture abscess and inflamed gingiva).
Follow up received on 30 Nov 2012 from physician via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Procedure (speech therapy) and events (aseptic necrosis bone, heart mild bradycardiac, cat bite to right hand, leukocytosis, dysarthria, small retention of cysts in the floor of the left maxillary sinus and urinary tract symptoms) were updated.
Follow-up received on 05 Dec 2012 from consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Therapy details of Aredia and Zometa updated. Events updated: bronchitis, conjunctivitis, viral upper respiratory tract infection, hyperthyroidism and facial swelling.
Refer case PHEH2012US017752.
summary.sendercomment: MAC: Review of available data reported in this legal case does not allow for proper causality assessments. Treatment dates with Zometa are not reported. Some conditions found in the report may not have developed under treatment with the product. The patient's events may be attributable to the underlying malignancy.
